Key Match Events: Tyrese Maxey scored the go-ahead basket with 23.7 seconds left and finished with 29 points to lead the Philadelphia 76ers to a 109-103 win over the Washington Wizards.
Guerschon Yabusele scored 21 points and blocked a potential tying layup with 14 seconds left to preserve the win for the Sixers.
Eric Gordon hit the tying 3 for the Sixers.
Maxey hit 11 of 27 shots and had six assists for the Sixers.
Jared Butler scored 26 points for the Wizards and Corey Kispert had 23.
Post-Match Reflections: The fans who did attend the game — including 'Party of Five' actor Scott Wolf — saw Maxey go off late.
Maxey, an All-Star last season, struggled at times as the go-to scorer this season with Embiid and George out so often.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Tickets on the secondary market were going for less than $10 each in the lower 100 level right before tipoff.
